## Overview

Promote `usePulsePresets` from `features/onboarding/model/` to `entities/pulse/model/` so multiple features can legally import it (FSD: features → entities is valid; cross-feature model imports are forbidden). Create the new `usePulsePresetDialog` Zustand store for cross-feature coordination.

## Step 1 — Move usePulsePresets

Create `apps/client/src/layers/entities/pulse/model/use-pulse-presets.ts` with:

```typescript
import { useQuery } from '@tanstack/react-query';
import { useTransport } from '@/layers/shared/model';
import type { PulsePreset } from '@dorkos/shared/types';

export type { PulsePreset } from '@dorkos/shared/types';

/** Fetch available Pulse schedule presets from the server. */
export function usePulsePresets() {
  const transport = useTransport();
  return useQuery<PulsePreset[]>({
    queryKey: ['pulse', 'presets'],
    queryFn: () => transport.getPulsePresets(),
  });
}
```

The existing file at `apps/client/src/layers/features/onboarding/model/use-pulse-presets.ts` re-exports from the new location:

```typescript
// Deprecated shim — import from entities/pulse instead.
export { usePulsePresets } from '@/layers/entities/pulse';
export type { PulsePreset } from '@/layers/entities/pulse';
```

This shim keeps `PulsePresetsStep` compilable without a simultaneous change to it (the shim is replaced in task 1.3).

## Step 2 — Create usePulsePresetDialog

Create `apps/client/src/layers/entities/pulse/model/use-pulse-preset-dialog.ts`:

```typescript
import { create } from 'zustand';
import type { PulsePreset } from '@dorkos/shared/types';

interface PulsePresetDialogState {
  /** Preset to pre-populate when dialog opens externally, or null for blank form. */
  pendingPreset: PulsePreset | null;
  /** True when the dialog was triggered externally (e.g., from SchedulesView sidebar). */
  externalTrigger: boolean;
  /**
   * Signal PulsePanel to open CreateScheduleDialog at form step with this preset.
   *
   * @param preset - The preset to pre-populate the form with
   */
  openWithPreset: (preset: PulsePreset) => void;
  /** Reset after the dialog has consumed the pending state. */
  clear: () => void;
}

export const usePulsePresetDialog = create<PulsePresetDialogState>((set) => ({
  pendingPreset: null,
  externalTrigger: false,
  openWithPreset: (preset) => set({ pendingPreset: preset, externalTrigger: true }),
  clear: () => set({ pendingPreset: null, externalTrigger: false }),
}));
```

